The paper discusses techniques for protecting intellectual property in chip design, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of logic locking, layout camouflaging, and split manufacturing, which are techniques related to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also mentions the involvement of untrusted entities in the supply chain, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and embedded systems (cs.ET).
